    "CM is the reverse-engineering of human cognition (an explanation of the causal mechanism).",
    "A T3 is meant to have cognitive capacities identical to and indistinguishable (to any human thinker) from the capacities of any human thinker.",
    "Not only are these different motivations and criteria, but they make it clear that the notion of designing a hybrid T3/GPT could only be AI, not CM, GPT-4: Your distinction between AI (Artificial Intelligence) as computational tools and CM (Cognitive Modeling) as the reverse-engineering of human cognition does highlight the inherent incoherence in the concept of a hybrid T3/GPT system: AI as a Tool: In the AI perspective, the primary goal is to create systems that can perform tasks, solve problems, and assist in thinking, often exceeding human capabilities in specific domains.",
    "The hybrid T3/GPT model, in this context, is an AI endeavor.",
